~ Rose Gold Color Therapy ~ 

My Boo @Mennia Switched up from the Big Chop Journey to the Color Journey. 👌🏿 I like the Switch up ! 
I feel that colors have a significant impact on our mood. We don’t pay attention to it but some colors we choose to wear can actually cancel out some moods. Just like we cancel out yellow with Violet. 
It’s good to be aware of the energies that a particular color has because you don’t want to much of something you don’t need. If you are a bold person and like to be athletic and moving around all the time than Red could increase that energy and you could have to much of it making you over stimulated. 
On the other hand if you are more subdue or less action oriented , then Red could actually give you what you need by increasing more action and boldness into your life. 
It’s easy to switch it up with your clothes but when you decide to turn your hair a new color then it may require a little more consideration. Something to think about next time you are about to make such a long lasting change 😉

This was my mother's biggest lesson to me, be honest with your fragility and don't let anybody take it. One of the most poignant memories I have with my mother that's branded in my memory, she was crying one day and I was trying to get her to stop, she turned to me with the sternest look in her eyes and said "don't you ever stop me from crying. I've earned my tears and I need to let it out" everything clicked in that moment. There's strength in being honest with who you are, crying is not a sign of weakness but of strength, it's weakness to hold it in and hide behind the mask and causing chaos. Diamond may be created under pressure but treated like their fragile. I'm fragile and I love it.
